# Click Trainer v2.7.1
A rewritten version of [d0sboots' click trainer](https://github.com/d0sboots/PerfectTower/blob/main/README.md#button-coordinate-finder).

It can auto seperate the tall screen data and wide screen data, making it less likely to mess up and insert a wrong datapoint.

Also uses a different way to process data, which is slower but allows more accurate formula under some cases.

## Modes
Edit the mode on the first line of the `main` script.
- `simple`: Produces regular data that works for all resolution and constant ui size, faster. Need dynamic ui off and ui size setting at a constant value.
- `manual`: Produces more data that works for different ui sizes, slower. Need dynamic ui off, and constantly changing the ui size setting.
- `dynamic`: Same as `manual`, but need dynamic ui on when recording data, therefore don't need to change the ui size setting.

**Note: When using `dynamic` mode, screen resolution larger and smaller than `1024x768` are both needed, or you would keep getting the `Need more datapoints` error.**
